+{"id":"bd-pz3jr","title":"P0: qgcvt writes past tracked small output buffer","description":"[CRITICAL] The qgcvt ABI wrapper writes a formatted decimal string directly into the caller's raw buf without consulting malloc_abi::known_remaining(buf) or otherwise bounding the write by tracked allocation size.\n\nEvidence:\n- crates/frankenlibc-abi/src/stdlib_abi.rs:4834 accepts raw caller buf.\n- crates/frankenlibc-abi/src/stdlib_abi.rs:4838 formats with ndigit.max(0) precision, so the output length is input-dependent.\n- crates/frankenlibc-abi/src/stdlib_abi.rs:4840-4843 copies bytes.len() bytes plus a trailing NUL into buf with ptr::copy_nonoverlapping and *buf.add(copy_len)=0.\n- Unlike safer tracked-buffer surfaces in this ABI crate, qgcvt does not cap by known_remaining or reject too-small tracked allocations.\n\nRepro shape: p = malloc(1); call qgcvt(123.456, 10, p). Expected hardened/TSM behavior is to cap to known_remaining(p) or reject safely. Actual code writes the full formatted string plus NUL through a 1-byte tracked allocation.\n\nFix direction: mirror the tracked-buffer cap being planned for gcvt: compute known_remaining(buf as usize), bound the writable length when known, and add an ABI regression with malloc-backed 1-byte and 2-byte buffers.","status":"closed","priority":0,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"codex-qgcvt-bounds","created_at":"2026-04-29T06:53:16.090203844Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-29T07:16:39.410443796Z","closed_at":"2026-04-29T07:16:39.410443796Z","close_reason":"fixed: qgcvt caps malloc-tracked output buffers with known_remaining; validation: stdlib_abi_test qgcvt, cargo check/clippy -p frankenlibc-abi, UBS","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["qgcvt","safety","stdlib"]}
